      "content": "i know about the hotlines, but they just want to talk me out of how i feel. they try to make me feel like there's some big bright future waiting if i just stick it out, but i don't see it. i'm just so done with the struggle. it feels like i'm just running in place while everyone else moves ahead, and the only real way to get some actual, permanent rest is to just leave it all behind. does that even make sense? that wanting to just end the struggle feels more like seeking peace than anything else?",
